11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment amends the resolve to provide that the Department of Public Safety,
1133 Office of the State Fire Marshal is required to initiate the program to compile an inventory
1144 of aqueous film-forming foam concentrate in the State no later than November 1, 2025 and,
1155 no later than January 1, 2028, submit the completed inventory to the joint standing
1166 committees of the Legislature having jurisdiction over environment and natural resources
1177 matters and criminal justice and public safety matters. The amendment authorizes either
1188 of those committees to report out legislation relating to the inventory to the Second Regular
1199 Session of the 133rd Legislature and directs the Office of the State Fire Marshal to make
2200 the completed inventory available on its publicly accessible website. The amendment also
2211 adds an appropriations and allocations section.
